Hyenas are honest animals. They do not pretend to be something else while they gnaw off your leg. Hyenas are also true to their own kind. I am honored to be in the Hyena Pack. That's how we survived 'Nam. That's how we survive now. That's how we will survive in the future.<br><br>
Invertibrates are another matter. They have no backbone. They are not true to their own kind. They are isolated entities. Many live in deep oceanic trenches as shape shifting bags of protoplasm, constantly eating mud and excreting the same.<br><br>
My Grandfather always said that human nature often paralelled the animal world. He was right. <br><br>
Detonate Zulu  <br><br>

